@page
@model PrivacyModel
@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Privacy Policy";
}
<h1>@ViewData["Title"]</h1>

<p class="text-muted">TaskManager Admin Panel — Educational Project</p>

<h2 class="h5 mt-4">1. Data We Process</h2>
<p>
    This application stores administrator account data and task management data in MongoDB.
    Typical records may include usernames, user names/surnames, task titles, descriptions,
    tags, and task status metadata.
</p>

<h2 class="h5 mt-4">2. Purpose of Processing</h2>
<p>
    Data is processed only to support the core functionality of the TaskManager admin panel,
    including authentication, authorization, user management, and task operations.
</p>

<h2 class="h5 mt-4">3. Authentication and Security</h2>
<p>
    The app uses cookie-based authentication for admin access. Admin credentials are stored in
    MongoDB with password hashing via ASP.NET Core PasswordHasher. The app includes failed login
    tracking and temporary lockout to reduce brute-force risk.
</p>

<h2 class="h5 mt-4">4. Data Retention</h2>
<p>
    Data is retained for project and demonstration purposes. In a production deployment, retention
    periods should be defined by organizational and legal requirements.
</p>

<h2 class="h5 mt-4">5. Third-Party Components</h2>
<p>
    This project uses MongoDB and ASP.NET Core components. Review their official privacy and
    security documentation when deploying beyond local development.
</p>

<h2 class="h5 mt-4">6. Educational Use Notice</h2>
<p>
    This application was built as a university project. The current policy is provided for
    educational completeness and should be adapted before production use.
</p>
